<TITLE> Young man killed in Chandpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, Apr 26 (bdnews24.com)  The police recovered the slaughtered body of a young man at Sadullahpur of North Matlab upazila in Chandpur on Monday. The deceased has been identified as Suruj Mia, 18, son of Fazar Ali of Muktirkandi village. He was a 'rent-a-motorcycle' driver. Rustam Ali Shikdar, officer in-charge of North Matlab police station, told journalists that two youths called Suruj hired his motorbike from Pathan Bazar of Sadullahpur union on Sunday afternoon. Suruj has been missing since then, he said. Police recovered the body, identified by victim's brother Sukkur Ali, at Galimkha village and sent it to Chandpur Sadar Hospital for post-mortem. Police suspect that any drug peddler or mugger group might have killed him. The victim's father has filed a murder case. bdnews24.com/
